00:11:57,690 --> 00:11:59,559
I know a better teahouse.

243
00:11:59,559 --> 00:12:01,090
I wanted to bring you guys.

244
00:12:02,330 --> 00:12:03,960
Do you know her?

245
00:12:06,529 --> 00:12:08,269
- No. - Mom!

246
00:12:09,230 --> 00:12:10,370
"Mom?"

247
00:12:11,669 --> 00:12:12,799
Is she your daughter?

248
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:14,840
Didn't you say she was a history teacher?

249
00:12:15,169 --> 00:12:16,970
I quit that job a long time ago.

250
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:18,279
Now, I deliver food...

251
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:20,809
and take errand jobs every now and then.

252
00:12:21,509 --> 00:12:23,950
If you have plumbing issues,

253
00:12:24,049 --> 00:12:26,580
or you don't want to take out the trash, call me.

254
00:12:26,779 --> 00:12:28,220
I'll do your chores.

255
00:12:29,919 --> 00:12:31,320
She's optimistic.

256
00:12:31,889 --> 00:12:33,519
An errand-runner.

257
00:12:46,399 --> 00:12:47,840
Good work.

258
00:12:48,110 --> 00:12:50,409
It was so much fun.

259
00:12:50,409 --> 00:12:52,039
I think I was born for the camera.

260
00:12:53,110 --> 00:12:55,950
Ms. Han, you were loved when you were little, right?

261
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:57,919
- How did you know? - I could tell.

262
00:12:57,919 --> 00:12:59,149
You're right.

263
00:12:59,149 --> 00:13:01,519
My mom never got married,

264
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:02,649
then she gave birth to me,

265
00:13:02,649 --> 00:13:05,620
so all her love for her future husband came to me.

266
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:06,789
I'm a lucky girl.

267
00:13:10,190 --> 00:13:11,230
I'm going.

268
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:13,100
Good work. Are you going to the funeral?

269
00:13:14,970 --> 00:13:16,100
You little brat,

270
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:17,330
your sister just asked you a question.

271
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:19,539
Are you deaf or something, you idiot?

272
00:13:23,309 --> 00:13:24,879
Ms. Han?

273
00:13:27,879 --> 00:13:29,049
Oh, my gosh.

274
00:13:29,179 --> 00:13:30,379
That was an inner voice.

275
00:13:30,649 --> 00:13:32,720
I've been meditating so much lately...

276
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:35,350
that I could hear Director Kim's inner voice in my head.

277
00:13:35,490 --> 00:13:39,120
Then I added a short impersonation of Kim Soo Mi.

278
00:13:42,759 --> 00:13:44,629
I told you in the car that I was going.

279
00:13:44,899 --> 00:13:46,629
I didn't answer because you asked again.

280
00:13:46,899 --> 00:13:47,929
Bye.

281
00:13:47,929 --> 00:13:49,629
Take my car.

282
00:13:49,629 --> 00:13:50,940
It's raining.

283
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:52,340
He already has your keys.

284
00:13:57,009 --> 00:13:59,639
Then, I recommend this coffee.

285
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:01,509
What should I get?

286
00:14:01,509 --> 00:14:03,509
Americano? Latte?

287
00:14:09,389 --> 00:14:11,289
It feels so nice to smell coffee.

288
00:14:11,289 --> 00:14:14,529
I almost lost my mind drinking healthy tea all day.

289
00:14:15,789 --> 00:14:17,700
- Do you know her? - I've never seen her in my life.

290
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:20,970
I like

