00:14:21,169 --> 00:14:22,269
Would you like to order?

292
00:14:22,269 --> 00:14:25,899
I'm craving genuine coffee.

293
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:29,039
We actually added hand-drip coffee to the menu today.

294
00:14:29,309 --> 00:14:30,809
I'd recommend that one.

295
00:14:34,279 --> 00:14:35,580
I see.

296
00:14:35,879 --> 00:14:37,549
So, the smell was coming from that.

297
00:14:38,519 --> 00:14:41,490
Or you could try the new drink that we're promoting this month...

298
00:14:41,490 --> 00:14:42,789
I'll have hand-drip coffee.

299
00:14:42,789 --> 00:14:45,289
- Two cups, please. - Two cups of hand-drip coffee.

300
00:14:51,259 --> 00:14:53,259
Do you think I was wrong too?

301
00:14:54,929 --> 00:14:56,929
What was so wrong about calling my mom, Mom?

302
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:01,169
I'm not saying I'm absolutely right.

303
00:15:01,570 --> 00:15:03,240
But still.

304
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:06,639
Don't you think so?

305
00:15:07,809 --> 00:15:09,279
Why are you facing away from me?

306
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:13,879
Gosh.

307
00:15:17,789 --> 00:15:19,519
Guys, do you want to go to Jeju Island today?

308
00:15:19,519 --> 00:15:20,559
(Let's Drink, Ji Yeon)

309
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:29,600
- Sun Guk. - Where are you headed?

310
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,500
If you ask me, you'll have to give me a ride.

311
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,210
Excuse me.

312
00:15:37,309 --> 00:15:38,409
This is great.

313
00:15:38,409 --> 00:15:40,580
I was having such a hard time catching a cab.

314
00:15:41,049 --> 00:15:43,179
- Gosh, I'm such a lucky girl. - Where are you going?

315
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:45,379
- Jeju Island. - Jeju Island?

316
00:15:45,379 --> 00:15:49,490
That was the greatest reaction I've seen from you so far.

317
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:50,789
Would you like to come with me?

318
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:55,330
I'm joking. Let's go!

319
00:15:57,330 --> 00:16:01,129
Let's get away, just the two of us

320
00:16:01,529 --> 00:16:04,970
Get rid of all your worries

321
00:16:05,269 --> 00:16:08,940
Under the blue Jeju sky

322
00:16:08,940 --> 00:16:10,769
And the stars

323
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:21,750
You're back. I hope it wasn't too hard.

324
00:16:21,950 --> 00:16:23,250
Thank you very much.

325
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:26,019
- Bye. - Bye.

326
00:16:26,019 --> 00:16:27,389
Bye.

327
00:16:40,139 --> 00:16:41,309
Thank you.

328
00:16:48,509 --> 00:16:50,210
Whenever we want to,

329
00:16:50,210 --> 00:16:52,950
we take the subway for a few stops and arrive in Jeju Island.

330
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:54,950
(Tamna Restaurant)

331
00:17:00,659 --> 00:17:02,730
It might be in the middle of Seoul,

332
00:17:03,090 --> 00:17:06,500
but the food at this bar is authentic Jeju cuisine.

333
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:08,170
- Gosh. - Oh, that's sweet.

334
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:10,930
- Yes! - Nice!

335
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:14,069
Here is the horse mackerel soup.

336
00:17:14,869 --> 00:17:17,109
- Fried silver-stripe round herring. - Gosh, that's legit.

337
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:20,609
- It looks great. - Shall I pour you girls a drink?

338
00:17:20,609 --> 00:17:21,750
- Yes! - Sounds good.

339
00:17:22,809 --> 00:17:24,309
Here we go.

340
00:17:24,309 --> 00:17:27,279
We're off to Jeju Island.

341
00:17:27,279 --> 00:17:29,220
Yes! Soju bomb!

342
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:31,690
The owner here was the first person to teach us...

343
00:17:31,690 --> 00:17:33,559
that alcohol tasted different depending on who poured it.

344
00:17:33,559 --> 00:17:34,589
- With two hands? - All right!

345
00:17:37,359 --> 00:17:40,329
It looks so delicious.

346
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,799
Auntie, this is practically draft beer.

347
00:17:43,799 --> 00:17:45,539
Take a big gulp of that.

348
00:17:45,539 --> 00:17:46,799
- Thank you. - Gosh.

349
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:49,910
- All right. Let's drink! - Let's drink!

350
00:18:01,549 --> 00:18:04,150
Is this Jeju Island? Gosh, this is amazing.

351
00:18:04,589 --> 00:18:06,259
Oh, my goodness.

352
00:18:08,329 --> 00:18:12,230
You, fried silver-stripe round herring. Seriously?

353
00:18:12,559 --> 00:18:13,660
Hey, try the horse mackerel soup.

354
00:18:15,099 --> 00:18:17,430
- This is the perfect hangover cure. - It's so good, isn't it?

355
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:20,269
- Her food keeps getting better. - I know.

356
00:18:20,670 --> 00:18:22,109
(Don't answer)

357
00:18:24,910 --> 00:18:25,910
Hey, isn't that your mom?

358
00:18:25,910 --> 00:18:27,680
Why is she calling Ji Goo and not us?

359
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,680
I know. Is there something wrong?

360
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:30,809
Nothing is wrong.

361
00:18:30,809 --> 00:18:32,619
- Still, you should answer that. - It's fine.

362
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:35,490
- Hey! - I answered it.

363
00:18:36,390 --> 00:18:37,420
Good.

364
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:41,859
You call your mom too.

365
00:18:41,859 --> 00:18:44,190
What are you doing? I called her this morning.

366
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,400
That was your mom calling you. Here.

367
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,630
She's sleeping right now.

368
00:18:48,470 --> 00:18:49,599
Gosh.

369
00:18:50,029 --> 00:18:51,400
Hello? Mom?

370
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:54,569
Ji Yeon was playing around and called you.

371
00:18:54,869 --> 00:18:56,309
I didn't wake you, did I?

372
00:19:00,779 --> 00:19:03,450
Mom. Did you drink?

373
00:19:03,710 --> 00:19:05,750
My mom was drunk.

374
00:19:06,150 --> 00:19:07,720
With who at this hour?

375
00:19:08,049 --> 00:19:10,220
I just had a bit to drink in town.

376
00:19:10,220 --> 00:19:11,990
- You're not at home right now? - Goodness.

377
00:19:12,259 --> 00:19:13,890
I am home.

378
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:16,859
Why would you drink so much at home?

379
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,900
Is there something going on?

380
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:25,400
Mom.

381
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,769
Yes? What?

382
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:31,710
Do you drink like this on your own every night?

383
00:19:32,140 --> 00:19:33,809
I told you, it's not like that.

384
00:19:34,710 --> 00:19:36,380
I am right.

385
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:40,819
Gosh, this is so annoying.

386
00:19:42,220 --> 00:19:43,319
Mom...

387
00:19:49,759 --> 00:19:51,930
How could you do this to me?

388
00:19:51,930 --> 00:19:54,869
How could you?

389
00:19:56,829 --> 00:19:59,200
Why must I live like this because of you?

390
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:02,440
Why? What did I do so wrong to you?

391
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:04,980
I went through the trouble of giving birth to you and raising you.

392
00:20:04,980 --> 00:20:07,039
But you just decided to cut me out of your life as you pleased.

393
00:20:07,279 --> 00:20:10,049
You didn't show your face once, and you looked down on your parents.

394
00:20:10,049 --> 00:20:11,779
You just live however you want.

395
00:20:11,779 --> 00:20:15,490
Since when did you greet me so cheerfully?

396
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:17,819
Is it fun for you to torment me?

397
00:20:18,289 --> 00:20:20,920
Do you know how loose-lipped those women are?

398
00:20:21,289 --> 00:20:22,930
It's one thing for your life to be embarrassing.

399
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:25,859
Why would you make my life embarrassing as well?

400
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:29,500
Why are you making your brother's life embarrassing too?

401
00:20:48,690 --> 00:20:50,049
Do you need a smoke?

402
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:53,220
No, you're smoking one for me.

403
00:20:54,630 --> 00:20:57,490
My mom only needs a cigarette and a cup of coffee.

404
00:20:57,730 --> 00:20:59,829
Still, if I knew today was such a day,

405
00:20:59,829 --> 00:21:01,769
I would've at least made some pork noodles.

406
00:21:01,769 --> 00:21:04,599
You know my mom's death anniversary rites are like spontaneous parties.

407
00:21:06,369 --> 00:21:10,210
It was about a year and a half after Ji Yeon's mom had passed away.

408
00:21:11,210 --> 00:21:12,210
What?

409
00:21:12,210 --> 00:21:13,509
- Let's drink. - Okay.

410
00:21:13,509 --> 00:21:15,309
(4 years ago, one summer day)

411
00:21:15,309 --> 00:21:16,980
They gave us an extra glass.

412
00:21:16,980 --> 00:21:18,180
- Really? - Yes.

413
00:21:18,349 --> 00:21:19,950
Then let's make that my mom's glass.

414
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:23,019
What?

415
00:21:23,349 --> 00:21:24,589
Is today your mom's death anniversary?

416
00:21:24,589 --> 00:21:27,920
Come on, her mom passed away in late fall...

417
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,789
Wait, no. Her death anniversary already passed.

418
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:30,890
Did it?

419
00:21:30,890 --> 00:21:32,529
Didn't you hold your mom's death anniversary rites?

420
00:21:33,759 --> 00:21:34,900
You're crazy.

421
00:21:35,269 --> 00:21:36,799
Didn't I tell you?

422
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,740
My mom said...

423
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:41,000
she didn't want me to remember the day she died...

424
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,009
if it was homework.

425
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:44,069
So she wanted me to forget her death anniversary.

426
00:21:44,539 --> 00:21:45,640
Really?

427
00:21:46,809 --> 00:21:48,150
But you know how the moment you try to forget it,

428
00:21:48,150 --> 00:21:49,579
you totally remember?

429
00:21:49,579 --> 00:21:52,279
It's like deleting your ex's number, but you suddenly have it memorized.

430
00:21:52,279 --> 00:21:55,519
That was your mom playing a trick since you always forget everything.

431
00:21:55,519 --> 00:21:57,750
She wanted you to remember her death anniversary at least.

432
00:21:57,750 --> 00:21:59,720
That's right. Your mom was smart.

433
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:02,359
But you know, I really forgot.

434
00:22:02,359 --> 00:22:04,700
I couldn't remember, no matter how hard I tried. Isn't it incredible?

435
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:08,200
I really must be an idiot. What do I do?

436
00:22:09,269 --> 00:22:10,430
Gosh, this is getting old.

437
00:22:10,430 --> 00:22:12,670
The tree frog listened to his mom's dying wish.

438
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:16,039
He buried her by the stream and cried whenever it rained.

439
00:22:16,539 --> 00:22:19,240
But Ji Yeon listened to her mom's dying wish...

440
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:21,809
and forgot all about her death anniversary...

441
00:22:21,809 --> 00:22:23,349
and just kept on laughing.

442
00:22:25,279 --> 00:22:27,720
The rain must be over now.

443
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:30,250
Yes, you're right.

444
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,559
When I came to Seoul,

445
00:22:34,390 --> 00:22:36,990
I couldn't get used to the smell of the rain.

446
00:22:36,990 --> 00:22:39,730
Whenever it would rain, I'd feel so homesick.

447
00:22:40,299 --> 00:22:43,170
But now I don't remember the smell of rain in Jeju.

448
00:22:44,130 --> 00:22:45,869
Black herbal tea with an egg yolk.

449
00:22:47,140 --> 00:22:48,970
That's what my mom would say.

450
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:51,980
She said that if you put an egg yolk in black herbal tea,

451
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:53,940
it smelled exactly like the rain on Jeju Island.

452
00:22:56,079 --> 00:22:57,980
Your mom sure was a weirdo.

453
00:22:59,019 --> 00:23:02,119
But this morning, all the eggs I cracked had two yolks in them.

454
00:23:02,119 --> 00:23:03,490
All three of them.

455
00:23:10,289 --> 00:23:11,599
Here. Eat up.

456
00:23:11,829 --> 00:23:14,099
Gosh, there are two yellow yolks.

457
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:16,900
I feel bad for that egg.

458
00:23:17,369 --> 00:23:19,170
It's because a young chicken was laying eggs...

459
00:23:19,170 --> 00:23:21,369
and didn't know how, so this happened.

460
00:23:22,039 --> 00:23:24,269
Then is this a bad thing?

461
00:23:25,609 --> 00:23:26,740
Of course not.

462
00:23:26,740 --> 00:23:28,549
Did I ever dislike you?

463
00:23:28,549 --> 00:23:30,150
Am I a double-yolk egg?

464
00:23:30,910 --> 00:23:32,819
In the end, I couldn't eat it.

465
00:23:32,980 --> 00:23:34,480
It felt like I was eating myself.

466
00:23:35,319 --> 00:23:37,319
You made such a fuss. My goodness.

467
00:23:38,690 --> 00:23:41,829
But then, as soon as I got to work this morning,

468
00:23:41,829 --> 00:23:44,730
I sat in front of the camera because we had to shoot introductions.

469
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:47,299
And I suddenly thought of that.

470
00:23:47,529 --> 00:23:49,970
I once entered a singing contest when I was little.

471
00:23:50,099 --> 00:23:52,299
And my mom was right there just a moment ago,

472
00:23:52,569 --> 00:23:54,640
but then she suddenly disappeared.

473
00:23:56,410 --> 00:23:59,980
Was my mom embarrassed that I was a bar owner's daughter?

474
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,509
Hey, don't make me laugh.

475
00:24:02,509 --> 00:24:04,880
Do you think your mom would've been embarrassed by that?

476
00:24:05,650 --> 00:24:06,849
She'd say that...

477
00:24:06,849 --> 00:24:10,250
you were the smartest bar owner's daughter in the world.

478
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:12,819
She even told the neighbourhood mutt.

479
00:24:15,230 --> 00:24:16,859
I do think I'm smart.

480
00:24:17,490 --> 00:24:19,599
I knew the moment I saw this.

481
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:23,130
We actually added hand-drip coffee to the menu today.

482
00:24:23,130 --> 00:24:24,569
I'd recommend that one.

483
00:24:25,769 --> 00:24:29,210
It shouldn't suddenly appear here, but it did.

484
00:24:29,509 --> 00:24:31,369
Oh, this is from my mom.

485
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,309
Isn't it more elegant...

486
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,450
than spinning alcohol bottles?

487
00:24:39,849 --> 00:24:42,819
I mean, grinding coffee is just manual labour too.

488
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:45,460
Why does it seem so cool?

489
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:50,230
If I'm ever reborn, I want to be born as drip coffee.

490
00:24:56,829 --> 00:25:00,599
You must've missed her so much.

491
00:25:00,839 --> 00:25:04,170
Auntie, the horse mackerel soup was so good today.

492
00:25:04,339 --> 00:25:07,009
That was your mom's specialty.

493
00:25:07,809 --> 00:25:10,509
She and I both should've stayed in Jeju,

494
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:12,680
working in the sea.

495
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:17,049
I never got to take her back to Jeju before she died,

496
00:25:17,049 --> 00:25:18,589
and I'll forever feel sorry about that.

497
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,819
Come on. Do you know what my mom said...

498
00:25:20,819 --> 00:25:22,259
as she left Jeju?

499
00:25:22,359 --> 00:25:25,660
"Farewell, Jeju. I will never come back here as long as I'm living."

500
00:25:25,660 --> 00:25:27,059
"I'll come back once I'm dead."

501
00:25:27,059 --> 00:25:28,599
- Your mom said that? - Yes.

502
00:25:28,599 --> 00:25:29,769
How do you know that?

503
00:25:29,769 --> 00:25:30,970
I heard it.

504
00:25:31,799 --> 00:25:34,240
You were still in your mom's womb at the time.

505
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:36,210
That is how I know best.

506
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:38,279
I was the closest person to her.

507
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:39,710
Will you keep lying?

508
00:25:39,710 --> 00:25:40,740
It's the truth.

509
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:43,009
I remember everything that happened inside my mom's womb.

510
00:25:43,210 --> 00:25:45,119
When my mom went diving in the sea,

511
00:25:45,119 --> 00:25:48,650
I'd follow along and swing around holding my umbilical cord.

512
00:25:48,650 --> 00:25:50,549
I can remember swimming with her and everything.

513
00:25:51,859 --> 00:25:53,690
I told you to stop lying.

514
00:25:53,819 --> 00:25:56,259
I'm not lying. One day,

515
00:25:56,259 --> 00:25:57,789
- I was... - Ji Yeon always said...

516
00:25:58,130 --> 00:26:00,700
that she could remember the days...

517
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:02,970
when she was still in her mother's womb.

518
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:06,839
You can't really believe her since she forgets what she ate a day ago,

519
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:09,640
but some days, it does sound like the truth.

520
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,069
Gosh.

521
00:26:11,069 --> 00:26:13,539
Like mother, like daughter. My goodness.

522
00:26:14,579 --> 00:26:15,680
Gosh.

523
00:26:21,549 --> 00:26:23,289
What's up with this mood?

524
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:25,559
Did you find out that this is my mom's death anniversary rite?

525
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:29,460
Do you guys know?

526
00:26:29,559 --> 00:26:31,859
I take after my dad.

527
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,559
Your dad?

528
00:26:33,630 --> 00:26:34,799
Do you know who he is?

529
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:36,299
I don't know that.

530
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:39,170
But she said I had an IQ of 160 because I took after my dad.

531
00:26:39,799 --> 00:26:41,369
Auntie knows who your dad is too?

532
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,109
How would Auntie know that?

533
00:26:43,339 --> 00:26:46,609
But if I ever meet my dad, I'd recognize him right away.

534
00:26:46,609 --> 00:26:49,079
Why? I remember his voice.

535
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:51,480
From when you were in your mother's womb?

536
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,380
- Yes. - Sure, we believe you.

537
00:26:53,420 --> 00:26:55,420
- Of course. Drink up. - It's the truth.

538
00:26:55,420 --> 00:26:58,049
I know what someone looks like just by the sound of their voice.

539
00:26:58,049 --> 00:26:59,119
I can't believe that.

540
00:26:59,119 --> 00:27:00,190
You know I have the perfect pitch, right?

541
00:27:00,190 --> 00:27:01,420
The moment I hear someone's voice,

542
00:27:01,420 --> 00:27:02,759
I can picture the skull, cheekbones, collarbones, pubic bones,

543
00:27:02,759 --> 00:27:04,630
and the size of all those bones too.

544
00:27:05,029 --> 00:27:07,059
- Just drink. - Okay.

545
00:27:12,099 --> 00:27:15,069
I saw my mom on the street today, and she ignored me.

546
00:27:15,069 --> 00:27:16,210
Really?

547
00:27:16,210 --> 00:27:18,740
- Did she forget your face? - As if.

548
00:27:18,740 --> 00:27:20,980
She was embarrassed in front of her friends.

549
00:27:23,210 --> 00:27:26,079
She used to want to show me off so much when I was a teacher.

550
00:27:26,220 --> 00:27:27,819
But today, she was trying so hard to hide me.

551
00:27:29,650 --> 00:27:32,660
Hey, but you can't get upset with your mom over something like that.

552
00:27:32,660 --> 00:27:34,789
I know. I'm not upset at all.

553
00:27:34,819 --> 00:27:37,559
- Come on. You're obviously upset. - Right.

554
00:27:40,059 --> 00:27:41,230
Forget it.

555
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:44,829
Later on, I will never do the same thing...

556
00:27:46,099 --> 00:27:47,240
to my own kids.

557
00:27:47,339 --> 00:27:48,910
- You should have a daughter just... - You should have a daughter just...

558
00:27:49,210 --> 00:27:51,009
- Jinx. - Jinx.

559
00:27:51,009 --> 00:27:53,140
- Jinx. - Here.

560
00:27:56,109 --> 00:27:58,779
- Jinx. - Jinx.

561
00:28:02,119 --> 00:28:04,690
I seriously have zero interest in getting married.

562
00:28:05,519 --> 00:28:09,359
But I'm going to have a daughter just like me and show my mom.

563
00:28:09,359 --> 00:28:10,589
So I will...

564
00:28:11,289 --> 00:28:12,460
get married.

565
00:28:12,630 --> 00:28:15,299
- Get married? - Get married?

566
00:28:15,299 --> 00:28:16,930
Kang Ji Goo is talking about marriage?

567
00:28:16,930 --> 00:28:18,269
Sure, go ahead.

568
00:28:18,269 --> 00:28:21,839
I won't be nice to my kid when she's good at something or makes me proud.

569
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:28,309
When she's at her lowest point,

570
00:28:29,710 --> 00:28:31,009
and...

571
00:28:31,650 --> 00:28:34,650
when she has nothing to boast about and feels embarrassed,

572
00:28:36,119 --> 00:28:38,220
That's when I'll be the nicest.

573
00:28:42,259 --> 00:28:44,059
She saw her own daughter for the first time in a while.

574
00:28:44,059 --> 00:28:45,900
And she said, "I can't go on living because of you."

575
00:28:45,900 --> 00:28:47,930
"How could you do this to me?"

576
00:28:47,930 --> 00:28:50,869
"I can't even sleep, and I'm in and out of hospitals because of you."

577
00:28:50,869 --> 00:28:52,369
I won't say that.

578
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:55,369
"Have you been eating?"

579
00:28:56,069 --> 00:28:57,670
"Are you feeling ill at all?"

580
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:00,609
I'm going to say that stuff.

581
00:29:02,710 --> 00:29:04,210
Whenever we drank,

582
00:29:04,210 --> 00:29:06,319
we trash-talked our moms as if it were a race.

583
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:09,119
It's like we're in a competition to see whose mom is the worst.

584
00:29:09,390 --> 00:29:10,549
Thank you.

585
00:29:10,549 --> 00:29:12,490
- Would our moms know? - I don't get it!

586
00:29:12,490 --> 00:29:14,619
That we talk badly about them so often?

587
00:29:14,619 --> 00:29:17,859
I mean, I have plenty to say too, you know?

588
00:29:17,859 --> 00:29:19,099
- Gosh. - Hey.

589
00:29:19,230 --> 00:29:21,970
She always pretends like she's not sick or having a hard time.

590
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:24,599
You...

591
00:29:24,599 --> 00:29:28,240
Do you know how annoying that can be?

592
00:29:28,569 --> 00:29:32,740
She's going to get caught in the end anyway.

593
00:29:32,910 --> 00:29:36,309
Or else, I'm the only one who becomes a bad person like today.

594
00:29:36,309 --> 00:29:39,380
It's to prevent you from being worried.

595
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:40,380
- For goodness' sake. - Gosh.

596
00:29:40,380 --> 00:29:43,990
Then don't answer the phone. Why would she answer?

597
00:29:43,990 --> 00:29:45,019
Hey.

598
00:29:45,119 --> 00:29:49,259
How can she ignore your call?

599
00:29:49,430 --> 00:29:51,630
At least your mom is...

600
00:29:51,859 --> 00:29:54,660
not telling you that she's going through a tough time.

601
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:57,000
- That's what a mom does. - Hey.

602
00:29:57,170 --> 00:29:59,900
If she's always telling you that she has sleep problems...

603
00:29:59,900 --> 00:30:01,200
because of you,

604
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:05,109
or that you're the reason she always has panic attacks...

605
00:30:05,109 --> 00:30:08,650
as if she'll die tomorrow...

606
00:30:08,809 --> 00:30:11,509
and making the daughter feel bad...

607
00:30:11,509 --> 00:30:13,519
is that a mom?

608
00:30:13,519 --> 00:30:17,619
If she's a real mom, she should tell her daughter.

609
00:30:17,619 --> 00:30:21,420
Hey, real moms can't say those things to their daughters.

610
00:30:21,420 --> 00:30:22,589
- Hey! - What?

611
00:30:22,759 --> 00:30:24,930
Stop talking!

612
00:30:25,299 --> 00:30:27,160
I don't even have a mom.

613
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:29,470
Why did she have to say that?

614
00:30:29,470 --> 00:30:32,269
- Oh, seriously. - I'm sleepy.

615
00:30:32,670 --> 00:30:34,670
Hey! I don't have a father!

616
00:30:34,670 --> 00:30:36,740
Hey! I didn't have one since birth.

617
00:30:36,740 --> 00:30:39,079
- Why are they doing this? - You're right.

618
00:30:39,079 --> 00:30:42,450
I'm sorry. I apologize.

619
00:30:42,450 --> 00:30:44,349
- You weirdos! - Oh, gosh.

620
00:30:44,349 --> 00:30:45,549
Go home now!

621
00:30:45,549 --> 00:30:46,549
- We have to go? - Why?

622
00:30:46,549 --> 00:30:49,589
After having daughters like you all,

623
00:30:49,589 --> 00:30:52,960
your mothers still cooked and ate seaweed soup.

624
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:55,589
No, my mom hates seaweed soup.

625
00:30:55,589 --> 00:30:59,460
For goodness' sake. Good for you.

626
00:30:59,930 --> 00:31:02,170
I'm fed up with you all.

627
00:31:02,170 --> 00:31:05,569
- Auntie, the food was so delicious. - Right.

628
00:31:05,569 --> 00:31:07,440
Thank you.

629
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:10,269
- The menu was great. - Takeout, please

630
00:31:10,269 --> 00:31:11,369
For goodness' sake.

631
00:31:16,410 --> 00:31:19,450
- Let's go. - What's this?

632
00:31:19,450 --> 00:31:20,779
You're drunk.

633
00:31:22,049 --> 00:31:24,750
Ms. An, you'll end up at a dog house today.

634
00:31:25,390 --> 00:31:26,819
Excuse me.

635
00:31:26,819 --> 00:31:29,089
- You shouldn't hold my head. - Sir.

636
00:31:29,089 --> 00:31:31,359
- You can't hold my head like that. - Sir.

637
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:34,900
- You all drank too much. - Yes. We did.

638
00:31:34,900 --> 00:31:36,599
Why did you drink so much?

639
00:31:36,599 --> 00:31:38,200
Aren't you our driver?

640
00:31:40,970 --> 00:31:42,670
Straighten your legs. Straighten them.

641
00:31:43,140 --> 00:31:45,710
Oh, my. I don't know you.

642
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:51,450
You obnoxious people.

643
00:31:55,349 --> 00:31:56,789
What's that?

644
00:31:57,190 --> 00:31:58,519
(Memorandum: No drinks during the day,)

645
00:31:58,519 --> 00:31:59,720
(during the weekends, and overnight if possible.)

646
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:01,559
They should know the meaning of a memorandum.

647
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,289
For goodness' sake.

648
00:32:03,730 --> 00:32:06,500
Sometimes, we need to drink.

649
00:32:07,529 --> 00:32:08,670
Like today.

650
00:32:09,529 --> 00:32:12,200
On days when we miss our moms.

651
00:32:14,339 --> 00:32:15,339
No, I mean...

652
00:32:15,339 --> 00:32:17,309
When we drink and talk badly about our moms,

653
00:32:17,740 --> 00:32:20,240
we don't understand our moms...

654
00:32:20,579 --> 00:32:22,579
but understand each other's moms.

655
00:32:22,579 --> 00:32:24,049
I'm sorry because...

656
00:32:24,049 --> 00:32:26,819
- What they said was all right. - I think she made me feel sorry.

657
00:32:26,819 --> 00:32:31,019
Why is she drinking alone?

658
00:32:31,019 --> 00:32:35,460
But she pretends as if nothing is wrong in front of me.

659
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:39,930
It's all because she doesn't want you to worry.

660
00:32:41,559 --> 00:32:43,730
(Call log: My daughter)

661
00:32:46,369 --> 00:32:47,500
So Hee.

662
00:32:47,970 --> 00:32:52,039
I had a drink with the other aunties at a neighbourhood feast.

663
00:32:52,339 --> 00:32:55,380
So don't worry about me.

664
00:32:55,609 --> 00:32:56,779
Okay?

665
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:00,750
Do you know what my mom was like?

666
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:02,549
One day,

667
00:33:02,990 --> 00:33:08,289
she said she'd be jealous and lonely if I got married...

668
00:33:08,289 --> 00:33:11,089
and told me not to get married. You know?

669
00:33:11,430 --> 00:33:13,130
Is that what a mom should say?

670
00:33:13,130 --> 00:33:16,430
She said that because she was worried you'd meet...

671
00:33:16,430 --> 00:33:19,269
any man and get married.

672
00:33:20,069 --> 00:33:21,140
Mom.

673
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:23,839
Hey.

674
00:33:24,809 --> 00:33:28,140
Tell my daughter's future husband...

675
00:33:31,079 --> 00:33:32,180
that I know...

676
00:33:34,319 --> 00:33:36,990
that he's marrying her because she's pretty...

677
00:33:40,019 --> 00:33:42,190
and that he has great taste.

678
00:33:43,859 --> 00:33:44,930
In my eyes too...

679
00:33:46,230 --> 00:33:48,599
she's so pretty.

680
00:33:49,930 --> 00:33:51,230
So...

681
00:33:53,369 --> 00:33:54,500
please...

682
00:33:56,970 --> 00:33:58,980
love her forever.

683
00:34:00,579 --> 00:34:02,309
Until she gets old...

684
00:34:03,980 --> 00:34:06,549
and doesn't look pretty anymore.

685
00:34:10,949 --> 00:34:14,260
I won't be nice to my kid when she's good at something or makes me proud.

686
00:34:15,860 --> 00:34:18,289
When she's at her lowest point,

687
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:22,300
and...

688
00:34:23,769 --> 00:34:26,570
when she has nothing to boast about and feels embarrassed...

689
00:34:26,570 --> 00:34:28,969
That's when I'll be the nicest.

690
00:34:30,670 --> 00:34:33,340
Ji Goo, your mom...

691
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:37,710
would've wanted to say the same.

692
00:34:37,710 --> 00:34:38,849
My mom?

693
00:34:49,659 --> 00:34:51,260
Everyone called my daughter...

694
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:57,670
a genius when she was young.

695
00:34:59,239 --> 00:35:03,010
She was good at painting and singing.

696
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:05,269
She was good at sports too.

697
00:35:05,679 --> 00:35:06,780
But...

698
00:35:07,809 --> 00:35:10,980
do you know when I was proud of her the most?

699
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:16,719
It was when she was about 200 days old.

700
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:22,860
She was so little crawling here and there.

701
00:35:23,630 --> 00:35:26,030
So I was very tired...

702
00:35:26,429 --> 00:35:28,730
and left her on the sofa.

703
00:35:29,969 --> 00:35:31,099
Oh, gosh.

704
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:35,639
She saw me cleaning from afar...

705
00:35:36,570 --> 00:35:40,510
and suddenly turned her back to climb down the sofa.

706
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:47,420
Then she looked at me and came crawling...

707
00:35:53,119 --> 00:35:54,559
towards me.

708
00:35:58,090 --> 00:36:00,960
I was so happy.

709
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:03,400
